{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"XMLSerializer","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XMLSerializer","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XMLSerializer\"><code>XMLSerializer</code></a></strong></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <code>XMLSerializer</code> interface provides the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XMLSerializer/serializeToString\" title=\"serializeToString()\"><code>serializeToString()</code></a> method to construct an XML string representing a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Glossary/DOM\">DOM</a> tree.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"methods","title":"Methods","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"serializetostring\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XMLSerializer/serializeToString\" title=\"serializeToString()\"><code>serializeToString()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns the serialized subtree of a string.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"serializing_xml_into_a_string","title":"Serializing XML into a string","isH3":true,"content":"<p>The first, basic, example just serializes an entire document into a string containing XML.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code> <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> s <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">XMLSerializer</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> d <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> document<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> str <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> s<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">serializeToString</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>d<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n <span class=\"token function\">saveXML</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>str<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This involves creating a new <code>XMLSerializer</code> object, then passing the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document\"><code>Document</code></a> to be serialized into <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XMLSerializer/serializeToString\" title=\"serializeToString()\"><code>serializeToString()</code></a>, which returns the XML equivalent of the document.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"inserting_nodes_into_a_dom_based_on_xml","title":"Inserting nodes into a DOM based on XML","isH3":true,"content":"<p>This example uses the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/insertAdjacentHTML\"><code>Element.insertAdjacentHTML()</code></a> method to insert a new DOM <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Node\"><code>Node</code></a> into the body of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document\"><code>Document</code></a>, based on XML created by serializing an <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element\"><code>Element</code></a> object.</p>\n<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect1\">\n  <p><strong>Note:</strong> In the real world, you should usually instead call <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/importNode\" title=\"importNode()\"><code>importNode()</code></a> method to import the new node into the DOM, then call one of the following methods to add the node to the DOM tree:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/append\"><code>Element.append()</code></a>/<a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/prepend\"><code>Element.prepend()</code></a> and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/append\"><code>Document.append()</code></a>/<a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/prepend\"><code>Document.prepend()</code></a> methods.</li>\n    <li>The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/replaceWith\"><code>Element.replaceWith</code></a> method (to replace an existing node with the new one)</li>\n    <li>The <a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!\"><code>Document.insertAdjacentElement()</code></a> and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/insertAdjacentElement\"><code>Element.insertAdjacentElement()</code></a> methods.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>\n<p>Because <code>insertAdjacentHTML()</code> accepts a string and not a <code>Node</code> as its second parameter, <code>XMLSerializer</code> is used to first convert the node into a string.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> inp <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> document<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">createElement</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'input'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token constant\">XMLS</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">XMLSerializer</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> inp_xmls <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token constant\">XMLS</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">serializeToString</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>inp<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// First convert DOM node into a string</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Insert the newly created node into the document's body</span>\ndocument<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>body<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">insertAdjacentHTML</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'afterbegin'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> inp_xmls<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The code creates a new <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input\"><code>&lt;input&gt;</code></a> element by calling <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/createElement\"><code>Document.createElement()</code></a>, then serializes it into XML using <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XMLSerializer/serializeToString\" title=\"serializeToString()\"><code>serializeToString()</code></a>.</p>\n<p>Once that's done, <code>insertAdjacentHTML()</code> is used to insert the <code>&lt;input&gt;</code> element into the DOM.</p>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/DOM-Parsing/#the-xmlserializer-interface","title":"DOM Parsing and Serialization"}],"query":"api.XMLSerializer"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.XMLSerializer","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XMLSerializer/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Guide/Parsing_and_serializing_XML\">Parsing and serializing XML</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XMLHttpRequest\"><code>XMLHttpRequest</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMParser\"><code>DOMParser</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Methods","id":"methods"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The XMLSerializer interface provides the serializeToString() method to construct an XML string representing a DOM tree.","popularity":0.0014,"modified":"2022-09-09T05:23:40.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"XMLSerializer","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"XMLSerializer","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"XMLSerializer","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"XMLSerializer","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/xmlserializer","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/xmlserializer/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/073f70e052ff92ab715df3c20678c11c9b51747f","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XMLSerializer","title":"XMLSerializer"}],"pageTitle":"XMLSerializer - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}